
[1]viciousness

   VI'CIOUSNESS, n.

   1. Addictedness to vice; corruptness of moral principles or practice;
   habitual violation of the moral law, or of moral duties; depravity in
   principles or in manners.

   What makes a governor justly despised, is viciousness and ill morals.

   2. Unruliness; refractoriness; as of a beast.
